Sasol will release its postponed financial results no later than 31 October, it said on Friday, The results for the year ended 30 June 2019 , were initially postponed from 19 August to 19 September 2019, to “allow for the completion of the assessment of possible internal control weaknesses identified during the independent review
announced by the board previously.” Sasol said on Friday that the board has “resolved to commission additional work under the independent review and to stipulate for in-depth investigation into certain aspects contemplated under the original scope….This work includes an assessment as to whether any identified control weakness and root cause of the changes in the cost and schedule of the Lake Charles Chemicals Project (LCCP) were present in the previous financial year and/or in the technology function of the Sasol group.”